 the period-spacing and mode-trapping\nproperties. Our results indicate that, in case of an eventual detection of\npulsating ultra-massive helium-rich white dwarfs, it would be possible to\nderive valuable information encrypted in the core of these stars in connection\nwith the origin of such exotic objects. The detection of pulsations in these\nstars has many chances to be achieved soon through observations collected with\nongoing space missions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 20 Dec 2020 15:40:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-10"}
